LONDON: The Arab coalition said on Tuesday that it hit several military targets in the Yemeni capital, Sanaa, state TV reported.
The coalition said it destroyed workshops for installing and equipping ballistic missiles, and a military communications system used to launch drones in the Bani Al-Harith district.
It also said that it destroyed another workshop for manufacturing and storing mines and weapons depots in Al-Thawra district, adding that preventive measures were taken to spare civilians and civilian objects from collateral damage.
Earlier on Tuesday, the coalition said it carried out “precision strikes on legitimate military targets in Sanaa,” and called on civilians not to gather or approach the targeted sites.
It added that the operation was in accordance with international humanitarian law and its customary rules.
The coalition also said it struck 26 Houthi targets in Marib and Al-Jouf during the past 24 hours, killing more than 150 fighters and destroying 18 military vehicles.